'''''To Hell and Back''''' is a [[platform game]] developed for the [[Commodore 64]] by [[Andy Jervis]] and published by [[CRL Group PLC|CRL]] in [[1988 in video gaming|1988]].<ref name="lemon">{{cite web|title=To Hell and Back|url=http://www.lemon64.com/?mainurl=http%3A//www.lemon64.com/games/details.php%3FID%3D2666|website=Lemon64}}</ref> Jervis' first game Moon Crystals was also included, although this was unmentioned in the game's packaging or press releases.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://archive.org/details/cvg-magazine-083/page/n53/mode/2up?view=theater|title=CVG Magazine Issue 083|date=September 1988}}</ref>

== Plot ==
The player is cast as Archangel Bertram who is trying to gain access to the Underworld by traveling around the Netherworld to retrieve the Ten Commandments stolen by Mephisto. Bertram starts his journey outside of the gates of Hell and must go deeper and deeper into the depths in order to confront Mephisto and destroy him.<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|url=https://archive.org/details/ToHellAndBack_C64|title=To Hell and Back video game manual|last=CRL Group|date=1988}}</ref>

== Gameplay ==
Bertram will be challenged by [[Ghost|ghosts]], [[Zombie|zombies]], and skeletons throughout the graveyard and the Netherworld.<ref name=":0" /> In this platform and maze game the screen will scroll as the player moves. The player must shoot various enemies with Archangel Bertram's halo and jump pits of spikes and lava over various levels. If the player was to touch an enemy the enemy will drain some of Bertram's energy. If Bertram comes into contact with spikes or lava or his energy reaches zero the player loses one of 8 lives. Occasionally the player will come across a [[bible]] which can restore some energy. At the end of each level is a boss which must be defeated in order to receive one of the Commandments back.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|url=https://www.mobygames.com/game/c64/to-hell-and-back|title=To Hell and Back for Commodore 64 (1988)|website=MobyGames|access-date=2019-05-08}}</ref>
As well as the main playing area the player can also see their score, lives, commandments collected and lives. A joystick is used to control Archangel Bertram.<ref name=":1" />

